<Base title="I Stand in Front of the Mirror Like Dog and Paint — Michalina Sablik">
  <div class="container page-content">
    <h1>I Stand in Front of the Mirror Like Dog and Paint</h1>
    <p class="exhibition-detail-venue">HOS Gallery | 2023</p>
    <div class="exhibition-detail-body">
      <p>Solo exhibition featuring Krysiak's "Headless Giantesses" series—large canvases depicting figures from circus and dreamlike contexts. The artist abandoned traditional oil painting in favor of materials that enabled therapeutic, meditative creation without preliminary sketches. She "dared to trust herself and her intuition" rather than planning compositions. Works emphasize scale and physical engagement, positioning depicted bodies as "radars of emotional states." Spontaneous execution where "once a line is drawn or a wrong move is made, it cannot be undone."</p>
    </div>
    <div class="exhibition-detail-credits">
      <p><strong>Artist:</strong> Maja Krysiak</p>
      <p><strong>Curator:</strong> Michalina Sablik</p>
      <p><strong>Coordinator:</strong> Katarzyna Piskorz</p>
    </div>
    <div class="exhibition-gallery" style="margin-top: 2.5rem; display: grid; gap: 1rem;">
